text: Psekups () is a rural locality (a khutor) in Adygeysk District of Adygea, Russia. The population was 907 as of 2018. There are 21 streets. == Geography == The khutor is located 4 km south from Adygeysk, 22 km south-east from Krasnodar and 100 km north-east from Maykop, on the left bank of the Bolshoy Dysh River. == Ethnicity == The khutor is inhabited by Circassians, Russians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Adygea
title: Psekups (rural locality)
